<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1452,1195,1366]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,294,1231,1257]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Luer" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[294,538,1231,1257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colothrix">
<emphasis box="[294,538,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Myoxanthus colothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[872,1085,1231,1257]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="parahybunensis">
<emphasis box="[872,1085,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">M. parahybunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the sheaths on the basal half of the ramicauls are completely covered with trichomes 
<emphasis box="[774,797,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. smooth, and it has a toothed white column 
<emphasis box="[1301,1324,1268,1293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. untoothed with purple wings and white oblong lip with a pair of conspicuous longitudinal keels emerging near the middle on the disc 
<emphasis box="[188,211,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. subpandurate lip with purple margins and microscopical keels on the disc.
</paragraph>
